# Enterprise Active Directory Home Lab

## Overview
This project documents the deployment of an enterprise-style Active Directory environment using Windows Server 2008, Windows clients, Kali Linux and Oracle VirtualBox.

The Objective was to simulate a corporate network by deploying Active Directory Domain Services(AD DS), configuring DNS, joining client systems to the domain, and perform LDAP enumeration from a security testing perspective.
---

## Objective

- Deploy Windows Server as an Active Directory Domain Controller.
- Configure DNS for Active Diretory.
- Configure static IP addressing.
- Join Windows client system to the domain.
- Create Users, Groups, and Organisational Units (OUs).
- verify domain authentication.
- Perform LDAP Enumeration from Windows.
- Document the deployment and troubleshooting process.


